<div class="docs-content__header">
  <span class="docs-content__eyebrow">Get Started</span>
  <h1 class="docs-content__title">Installation</h1>
  <p class="docs-content__description">Get Director running locally or deploy it to production. Choose the installation method that suits you best.</p>
</div>

<div class="prose">
  <h2 id="requirements">Requirements</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ruby 3.3+</strong></li>
    <li><strong>SQLite 3.35+</strong> — Director uses SQLite for everything: primary database, Solid Queue, Solid Cache, and Solid Cable</li>
    <li><strong>tmux</strong> — required for local adapters (Claude Code and OpenCode) which run agent sessions in isolated tmux panes</li>
  </ul>
  <p>No PostgreSQL, Redis, or other external services required. Director is designed to run self-contained on a single machine.</p>

  <h2 id="install-from-source">Install from Source</h2>
  <p>Clone the repository and run the setup script:</p>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/jorgegorka/director.git
cd director
bin/setup</code></pre>
  <p>The setup script installs dependencies, prepares the database, and creates the necessary SQLite databases for Queue, Cache, and Cable.</p>
  <p>Start the development server with all background processes:</p>
  <pre><code>bin/dev</code></pre>
  <p>This launches the Rails server, Solid Queue worker, and CSS build watcher via Foreman. Visit <code>http://localhost:3000</code> to access Director.</p>
  <p>Create an account, then create your first project to get started.</p>

  <h2 id="install-with-docker">Install with Docker</h2>
  <p>Director is available as a Docker image. Pull the latest version from the GitHub Container Registry:</p>
  <pre><code>docker pull ghcr.io/jorgegorka/director:latest</code></pre>
  <p>Run the container:</p>
  <pre><code>docker run -d \
  --name director \
  -p 3000:3000 \
  -v director_storage:/rails/storage \
  -e SECRET_KEY_BASE=your-secret-key \
  ghcr.io/jorgegorka/director:latest</code></pre>
  <p>The <code>-v</code> flag ensures your SQLite databases persist across container restarts. Visit <code>http://localhost:3000</code> once the container is running.</p>

  <h2 id="install-with-once">Install with ONCE</h2>
  <p><a href="https://github.com/basecamp/once" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ONCE</a> is Basecamp's tool for installing and managing self-hosted Rails applications. If you already have ONCE set up, you can use it to install and manage Director.</p>
  <p>ONCE handles provisioning, updates, and backups — making it the easiest way to run Director in production on your own server.</p>
  <p>Visit the <a href="https://github.com/basecamp/once" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ONCE repository</a> for setup instructions.</p>

  <h2 id="environment-variables">Environment Variables</h2>
  <p>For local agent adapters, you'll need API keys for the AI providers you plan to use:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><code>ANTHROPIC_API_KEY</code></strong> — required for Claude Code adapter</li>
    <li><strong><code>OPENAI_API_KEY</code></strong> — for OpenCode with OpenAI models</li>
    <li><strong><code>GEMINI_API_KEY</code></strong> — for OpenCode with Gemini models</li>
    <li><strong><code>GROQ_API_KEY</code></strong> — for OpenCode with Groq models</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Set these in your shell environment or in a <code>.env</code> file. Director forwards the relevant keys to agent processes automatically.</p>

  <h2 id="production-deployment">Production Deployment</h2>
  <p>Director ships with a <strong>Dockerfile</strong> and <strong>Kamal</strong> configuration for production deployment. Kamal handles container building, deployment, and zero-downtime restarts.</p>
  <p>Key production considerations:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Secret key base</strong> — set <code>SECRET_KEY_BASE</code> for session encryption</li>
    <li><strong>SQLite volumes</strong> — ensure persistent storage for your database files across container restarts</li>
    <li><strong>tmux availability</strong> — if using local adapters in production, ensure tmux is installed in the container</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Run the full CI suite before deploying:</p>
  <pre><code>bin/ci</code></pre>
  <p>This runs RuboCop, Brakeman security analysis, bundler-audit, importmap audit, and the full test suite.</p>
</div>
